HEADWORD: Pachyglossal
<hw>Pach`y*glos"sal</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧k`⟦icr⟧*gl⟦ocr⟧s"s⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pachy-</ets> + Gr. <grk>glw^ssa</grk>
tongue.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a thick tongue; -- applied
to a group of lizards (<fam>Pachygloss⟦ae⟧</fam>), including the iguanas
and agamas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

